<h2><br/>
Complexity72h</h2>
<p>Complexity72h is an interdisciplinary workshop for young researchers in complex systems. Participants form teams and carry out projects in a three days’ time, i.e. 72 hours. The goal of each team is to upload on the arXiv (or similar repositories) a report of their work by the end of the event. The editions of 2018 and 2019 were a success: 11 out of 11 projects became arXiv preprints and new collaborations were born. Complexity72h is back for a 2023 edition, which will take place in Palma (Mallorca, Spain) on June 26-30.</p>
<p>More info &amp; application: <a href="http://www.complexity72h.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">www.complexity72h.com</a> <br/>Deadline for applications: March 1st 2023</p>
